						               													<description>An economic game with auctions, bidding, stock market cards, landfill sites cards, trading between players, takeovers at stock market, waste deposits so on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Map of the game represents the big cities of the U.S. and EU. Each city has a huge garbage dump.  Each player starts with a certain amount of money. During the game, each will try to buy at auctions as many landfills.  The wastes, periodically obtained from these landfills are carried through the infrastructure which each player builds it. Each player must purchase their processing factories specialized in certain types of wastes. These processes the certain amount of waste and can also be upgraded. The prices of finished materials obtained from these factories are dictated by The Stock Exchange and by The Market (playing cards). Each player can also purchase shares at other players companies (directly from Stock Market or borrowing money to other players).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Profits must be invested in &amp;quot;Green Energy&amp;quot; (Solar Panel Plant, Wind Turbines, Bio Diesel Rafinery). For each such expensive investment, the player will receive &amp;quot;Green Points&amp;quot;.  After a fixed number of rounds the player who has the highest points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
